                "name": "Bob Davidson",
                "href": "/profile/Bob-Davidson-24"
            },
            "answer_text": "Absolutely you can. The shareholder in my first law firm\u2019s undergrad degree was in philosophy. Philosophy would be great prep for law. You will have covered logic and logical fallacies: law is very much about logical reasoning. Also philosophy is great for honing one\u2019s thought processes - very important for law. When it comes down to it, law schools are less concerned about a candidate\u2019s undergraduate degree and are more concerned about his/her potential to succeed in their programs. So they look at candidate\u2019s entire presentation before deciding whom to admit or reject. ",
            "date": "Answered January 24, 2020",
