                "name": "Michael Jacobs",
                "href": "/profile/Michael-Jacobs-74"
            },
            "answer_text": "Can I go to law school and become a lawyer with a philosophy degree? Sure! Why not? There is no specific undergraduate major required for admission to law school. Although some colleges offer \u201cpre-law\u201d courses, that is simply a \u201cmix\u201d of various courses that the college\u2019s administrators decided might be helpful with the concepts and thought processes needed for understanding and practicing the law. But that\u2019s like buying a box of pancake mix, instead of building your own pancake batter from scratch, containing the ingredients YOU want in it. People go into law from all kinds of different backgrounds. If something about practicing law appeals to you, go for it! ",
